ber of seas.\",\"64 is the number of classical arts listed in many Indian scriptures.\",\"555 is the number of keyboard sonatas written by Domenico Scarlatti, according to the catalog by Ralph Kirkpatrick.\",\"384 is the apogee (farthest distance from Earth) of the expeditions to the International Space Station in km.\",\"31 is the number of musical triads (12 major, 12 minor, 4 diminished, and 3 augmented).\",\"43 is the maximum number of cars participating in a NASCAR race in the Cup Series or Nationwide Series.\",\"164 is the number of episodes that the TV show The Adventures of Rin Tin Tin ran on ABC from 1954 to 1959.\",\"273 is the death toll of the air crash of American Airlines Flight 191.\",\"183 is the rank of Laos in countries by population density.\",\"366 is the number of days in a leap year.\",\"8 is the number of furlongs in a mile.\",\"235 is the number of three interstate highways in the United States, located in the states of Iowa, Kansas, and Oklahoma.\",\"144 is a gross (a dozen dozen).\",\"148 is the number of episodes of the TV series The Fresh Prince of Bel-Air on NBC from 1990 to 1996.\",\"47 is the total numbers of balloons that a player can collect in Rareware's Nintendo 64 game Diddy Kong Racing.\",\"83 is the highest UHF channel on older televisions made before the late 1970s.\",\"125 is years in a quasquicentennial.\",\"70 is the distance (meter) from archer to targets in Olympic Archery.\",\"142 is the number of staircases at Hogwarts School of Witchcraft and Wizardry, in the Harry Potter universe.\",\"334 is the long-time highest score in Test cricket (held by Sir Donald Bradman and Mark Taylor).\",\"61000 is the average number of people airborne over the US at any given hour.\",\"5300 is the number of gum wrappers that Steve Fletcher has, the record for the largest gum wrapper collection.\",\"169 is the number of miles that Thomas Sopwith, an English aviation pioneer flew in 3 hours, 40 minutes on December 18, 1910.\",\"214 is the number of Chinese radicals for the writing of Chinese characters according to the 1716 Kangxi Dictionary.\",\"166 is the feet above sea level at Turriff in Aberdeenshire, Scotland.\",\"13 is the number of Oscar nominations of actress Meryl Streep, who holds the record for the most Oscar nominated actress.\",\"1e+150 is the estimation of the game-tree complexity of xiangqi.\",\"26 is the number of letters in the English and Interlingua alphabets.\",\"1e+21 is the number of grains of sand on all the world's beaches put together.\",\"400 is the number of years in a period of the Gregorian calendar, of which 97 are leap years and 303 are common.\",\"1e+40 is the Eddington–Dirac number.\",\"81 is the number of stanzas or chapters in the Tao te Ching (in the most common arrangements).\",\"222 is the score in the 1916 Cumberland vs. Georgia Tech football game, with Georgia Tech winning 222-0, which was the record for most points scored by one team in an American football game.\",\"25 is the minimum age of candidates for election to the United States House of Representatives.\",\"61 is the number of points required to win a \\\"standard\\\" game of Cribbage.\",\"205 is the world speed record (mph) of a car on ice.\",\"480 is the number of hours for rocking non-stop in a rocking chair, a world record held by Dennis Easterling of Atlanta.\",\"538 is the total number of votes in the Electoral College of the United States.\",\"83 is the atomic number of bismuth.\",\"26 is the number of red cards as well as the number of blue cards in a normal deck of cards.\",\"198 is the rank of Marshall Islands in world population.\",\"214 is the number of Chinese radicals for the writing of Chinese characters according to the 1716 Kangxi Dictionary.\",\"68 is the ideal temperature (F) for developing black-and-white film.\",\"42 is the number of spots (or pips, circular patches or pits) on a pair of standard six-sided dice.\",\"85 is the IQ and nickname of Aaron in Alien 3.\",\"626 is the number of compositions of Wolfgang Amadeus Mozart, according to the Köchel Catalogue.\",\"200 is degrees in a human\\\"s field of vision (approximately).\",\"1000 is the number of elephants it took to bring in the material to build the Taj Mahal from various parts of India.\",\"400000000000 is the number of stars in the Milky Way galaxy.\",\"33 is the temperature at which water boils according to the Newton scale.\",\"124 is a stable isotope of tellurium.\",\"587 is the outgoing port for email message submission.\",\"160 is the number of characters permitted in a standard short message service in Australia and Europe.\",\"13 is the number of Oscar nominations of actress Meryl Streep, who holds the record for the most Oscar nominated actress.\",\"650000000 is the number of years that jellyfish have been on Earth, existing before sharks and dinosaurs.\",\"3500000000000 is the estimated population of fish in the ocean.\",\"390 is the speed in feet per second that nerve impulses for muscle position travel at.\",\"128 is the bytes of memory of the Atari 2600 console.\",\"80 is the length (years) of the Eighty Years' War (1568–1648).\",\"204 is the HTTP status code indicating the request was received but there is no response to the request.\",\"207 is the area code for the US state of Maine.\",\"25000000 is the number of different inhabited planets in the the Galactic Empire.\",\"1728 is braces were first invented by Pierre Fauchard.\",\"418 is the error code for \\\"I'm a teapot\\\" in the Hyper Text Coffee Pot Control Protocol.\",\"80 is a common limit for the characters per line in computing (derived from the number of columns in IBM cards).\",\"Infinity is the estimation of the game-tree complexity in the game of Go.\",\"154 is the period in days that the sun follows on gamma-ray flares.\",\"40000000 is the number of times lightning hits the ground 40 million times a year in the United States.\",\"54 is the number of countries in Africa.\",\"404 is the HTTP status code for 