 ocean.\",\"134 is the number of episodes in the TV series Hawaiian Eye that ran on ABC from 1959 to 1963.\",\"50000000000000000 is the total population in Isaac Asimov's Galactic Empire.\",\"227 is the number of days Pi Patel was at sea in the popular novel, Life of Pi.\",\"525998433 is the number of distinct websites as of November 2011.\",\"712 is the largest known number such that it and its 8th power have no common digits.\",\"14500 is the number of unique English words occur in the King James Version of the Bible.\",\"17000 is the length in km of bicycle lanes with special bicycle traffic lights in the Netherlands.\",\"5880000 is the number of geographic features named by the NIMA GEOnet Names Server.\",\"693 is the number of sections in Ludwig Wittgenstein's Philosophical Investigations.\",\"3000 is the number of years for which Carpenter ants have been used to close wounds in parts of India, Asia and South America.\",\"213 is the code for character \\\"Õ\\\" in codepages such as ISO-8859-1 and UTF-8.\",\"111 is the lowest positive integer requiring six syllables to name in American English, or seven syllables (including \\\"and\\\") in Canadian and British English.\",\"56 is the number of officially recognized ethnic groups in the list of ethnic groups in China.\",\"41 is the number of soldiers in The Expendables (2010 film) tactor Eric Roberts laments to his subordinates about having been killed by star Sylvester Stallone in his escape from their island.\",\"396 is the displacement in cubic inches of early Chevrolet Big-Block engines.\",\"6.022e+23 is the number of molecules in one mole of any substance (Avogadro's number).\",\"441 is the number of squares on a Super Scrabble board.\",\"197 is the approximate atomic mass of Gold.\",\"463 is the number of days in the synodic period of Ceres.\",\"202 is the HTTP status code indicating the request was accepted but has not yet been fulfilled.\",\"24 is the number of carats representing 100% pure gold.\",\"9801 